cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.DB 

This paper discusses the lack of location privacy in mobile crowdsourcing applications, which involves the collection of geo-located data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of existing location privacy-preserving mechanisms (LPPMs) on publicly available data, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DB (Databases). The paper also mentions the privacy concerns for users, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
